comments.message: Is it the same for the 9x50 ?

Yes.

Documentation:
sudo apt-get install build-essential chrpath coreutils cvs desktop-file-utils diffstat docbook-utils fakeroot g++ gawk gcc git git-core help2man libgmp3-dev libmpfr-dev libreadline6-dev libtool libxml2-dev make python-pip python-pysqlite2 quilt sed subversion texi2html texinfo unzip wget graphviz curl m4 libxml-simple-perl libxml-writer-perl geany scons libssl-dev libsqlite3-dev liblzo2-dev cifs-utils ssh

What's the default python version on 14.04 ?
Because that part might not be needed

libsqlite3-dev:i386 is also required for 9x50 and most likely other chipsets.

This pulls in the following:
Install: libsqlite3-dev:i386 (3.8.2-1ubuntu2.1), libgcc1:i386 (4.9.3-0ubuntu4, automatic), libc6:i386 (2.19-0ubuntu6.9, automatic), libsqlite3-0:i386 (3.8.2-1ubuntu2.1, automatic), linux-libc-dev:i386 (3.13.0-95.142, automatic), libc6-dev:i386 (2.19-0ubuntu6.9, automatic), gcc-4.9-base:i386 (4.9.3-0ubuntu4, automatic)

These are needed otherwise, the build tools are not able to find armcc even though it shows up via 'ls'.
It has something to do with running 32-bit libraries within the 64-bit 'exe'. I didn't investigate further and exactly which of the above packages fixes the issue.
